EULOGY 01 | Sit. The reading is brief, the verdicts briefer, and the estate has never once been kept waiting.
EULOGY 02 | BLUE gave 2 pennies to the ground and the tolls. Generosity is only ever involuntary here.
VERIFY_SNAP res://verify_out/stirs_f/snap_eulogy_13028.png
EULOGY 03 | GOLD hoarded 25 pennies and spent it on nothing. The manor respects the discipline; the will does not reward it.
EULOGY 04 | We commend RED, who bought 20 wreaths with other people's grief and now owns a house that owns them back.
EULOGY 05 | And MINT — who took from no one all night, and wept at two graves besides — was in the estate's estimation, almost kind.  How unusual.
EULOGY 06 | The estate adds, for the record: GOLD has been paid in blood money before. The ledger rounds up.
EULOGY 07 | The estate closes the ledger. Nothing is forgiven, but everything is filed, which the estate finds nearly the same.
